'''Eduardo Li Sánchez''' (born 11 November 1958) is a Costa Rican [[Association football|football]] administrator, [[FIFA]] executive committee member-elect, [[CONCACAF]] executive committee member, and the [[Costa Rican Football Federation]] (FEDEFUT) president. He co-founded [[Puntarenas F.C.]] with Adrián Castro Velásquez in June 2004. His paternal Chinese grandfather immigrated to Costa Rica in 1920.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ticotimes.net/2015/05/28/costa-ricas-soccer-chief-eduardo-li-asked-six-figure-bribe-says-fifa-indictment|title=FIFA-Gate: Costa Rica’s Eduardo Li allegedly received 6-figure bribe, says US indictment|work=The Tico Times}}</ref>
Li is involved in the [[2015 FIFA corruption case]], and was arrested in May 2015 in Switzerland to face [[corruption]] charges in the US.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Apuzzo|first1=Matt|last2=Schmidt|first2=Michael S.|last3=Rashbaum|first3=William K.|last4=Borden|first4=Sam|title=FIFA Officials Arrested on Corruption Charges; Blatter Isn’t Among Them|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/27/sports/soccer/fifa-officials-face-corruption-charges-in-us.html |publisher=New York Times|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> Li was banned by [[FIFA Ethics Committee]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/05/27/fifa-officials-banned_n_7453476.html |title=FIFA Officials Banned From Football-Related Activities In Wake Of Scandal |last1=Jauregui |first1=Andres |date=27 May 2015 |publisher=The Huffington Post |accessdate=17 July 2016}}</ref>
On 18 December 2015, he was extradited to the United States.<ref name="nacion">{{cite web|url=http://www.nacion.com/deportes/futbol-costa-rica/Eduardo_Li-Fedefutbol-FIFA_0_1531046947.html|publisher=nacion.com|title=Eduardo Li se declara inocente pero seguirá detenido en Estados Unidos|accessdate=10 September 2016}}</ref>
