'''Shahzad Ali Malik''' is a former President of [[Lahore]] [[Chamber of Commerce and Industry]]. He received the prestigious [[Sitara-i-Imtiaz]] Award by the [[President of Pakistan]] in 2013, the third-highest decoration given to any civilian in Pakistan, in recognition of his research work in the field of hybrid rice technology for higher and better yield of rice in Pakistan.<ref name=TheNation/><ref>http://www.dawn.com/news/742068/abida-parveen-aleem-dar-among-winners-posthumous-awards-for-manto-mehdi-hassan, Shahzad Malik's [[Sitara-i-Imtiaz]] Award info listed on [[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]] newspaper, Retrieved 3 July 2016</ref>

==Recognition by the business community==
The whole business community including 'Lahore Chamber of Commerce and Industry' and [[Rice Exporters Association of Pakistan]] applauded the decision of President [[Asif Ali Zardari]] for conferring of the Sitar-e-Imtiaz Award (Star of Excellence) Award on Ex-Chairman, Rice Exporters Association of Pakistan, also the founder member of this Association.<ref name=TheNation/>

Lahore Chamber of Commerce and Industry's President Farooq Iftikhar also commended his efforts for Agricultural Development in [[Pakistan]].<ref name=TheNation>{{cite web|title=The Nation|url=http://www.nation.com.pk/pakistan-news-newspaper-daily-english-online/business/26-Mar-2013/shahzad-malik-receives-sitara-i-imtiaz|publisher=Nawaiwaqt Group of Newspapers|accessdate=3 July 2016|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FkfkHFAl|archivedate=2013-04-09|deadurl=no}}</ref> He is the son of ''Muhammad Shafi Malik'', another recipient of this award in the past.

