{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox_Newspaper | name = Világgazdaság| image = | type = Business daily| format = [[Newspaper]] | foundation = {{start date and age|1969}}| owners = Mediaworks Hungary Zrt. | language = [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] | headquarters = [[Budapest]] | editor = Balint Deak | price = | website = [http://vg.hu/ vg.hu] | circulation = 13430 | }}
'''''Világgazdaság''''' (''World Economy'' in English) is the leading<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oecd.org/dataoecd/39/3/1818237.pdf|title=Portfolio Effects in Conglomerate Mergers|accessdate=29 May 2008|year=2001|publisher=OECD|page=156}}</ref> [[Hungary|Hungarian]] business daily<ref>{{cite web|title=Overview of Science Reporting in the EU (page 120)|work=Official website of the European Commission|url=http://ec.europa.eu/research/conferences/2007/bcn2007/overview_of_science_reporting_eu_en.pdf|date=2007|accessdate=29 May 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=World Newspapers and Magazines - Hungary|work=Worldpress|url=http://www.worldpress.org/newspapers/EUROPE/Hungary.cfm|accessdate=29 May 2008}}</ref> newspaper, operating as part of Mediaworks Hungary Zrt.The newspaper is traditionally issued on every [[Budapest Stock Exchange]] trading day.
==History and profile== ''Világgazdaság'' was founded in 1969.<ref name=bpost>[http://budapost.eu/vilaggazdasag-2/ Világgazdaság] ''Budapost''. Retrieved 6 December 2013.</ref> It is headquartered in [[Budapest]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Communicating Europe: Hungary Manual|url=http://www.esiweb.org/pdf/enlargement_debates_manual_hungary.pdf|publisher=European Stability Initiative|accessdate=26 November 2014|date=December 2010}}</ref>
The daily is called "the green newspaper" since it is published on green paper.<ref name=bpost/> During the [[Communism in Hungary|communist era in Hungary]] it was the first newspaper which was allowed direct access to Western [[news agencies]].<ref name=bpost/> Its sister publication is ''[[Heti Világgazdaság|Heti]]'', a weekly founded in 1979.<ref name=bpost/>
